# .leak-denylist.example — template for the pre-commit leak guard (.githooks/pre-commit).
#
# Copy to .leak-denylist (which is gitignored) and add the strings you never want
# to commit — typically your internal hostnames. One extended-regex per line;
# blank lines and full-line '#' comments are ignored (a '#' mid-line is part of
# the pattern). Matching is case-insensitive. A malformed regex here blocks the
# commit with a clear message rather than silently disabling the check.
#
# The built-in checks (the shared CI pattern set in .github/leak-patterns.txt —
# credentials, private/tailnet IPs, LEO-<number> and tracker-link refs) always
# run; these are EXTRA patterns on top.
#
# Replace the placeholders below with your own (do NOT commit the real file):
# myproj-db
# myproj-app
# myproj-edge
# internal-vm-[0-9]+
# \.my-tailnet-name\.ts\.net
